    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>What's wrong with this subheading from ''On Avenue C, Renewal and Regret'' (Aug. 3)?: ''Yuppies, squatters, Latinos and students seek a delicate balance.'' I'm Latino (and lived on Avenue C), also a graduate student and a young urban professional. I've never been a squatter.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>What's wrong with this subheading from ''On Avenue C, Renewal and Regret'' (Aug. 3)?: ''Yuppies, squatters, Latinos and students seek a delicate balance.'' I'm Latino (and lived on Avenue C), also a graduate student and a young urban professional. I've never been a squatter.</p>
        <p>Is it more acceptable to contrast Latinos, as opposed to other ethnic groups, with students and professionals?</p>
        <p>JOSEPH TROCHE  Hastings-on-Hudson, N.Y.</p>
      </block>
